Nhìn bằng tai, nghe bằng mắt - Bài luyện nghe 3 tốc độ
Câu chuyện về chàng trai bị mù màu dưới đây được kể bằng ba tốc độ - chậm, vừa và nhanh. Bạn có thể thử sức ở bất cứ tốc độ nào phù hợp với mình.
Bài luyện nghe tiếng Anh (Đề Listening 1)   /   Đề Listening 7: 'Gió bắt đầu từ đâu'?
Sau khi lựa chọn tốc độ nghe phù hợp với mình, bạn hãy thử sức và điền từ vào 20 chỗ trống trong câu chuyện dưới đây về Neil Harbisson, chàng trai không thể nhìn được bất cứ màu gì ngoại trừ màu xám.
Tốc độ nhanh
We see with our eyes and hear with our ears. At least that’s the conventional way to do things, but no one is ________(1) Neil Harbisson conventional. Neil is colorblind. Unlike many colorblind people, who are _______(2) to see just a few specific colors, like red or blue, Neil _______(3) see any colors ________(4) for grey. He has spent his whole life experiencing the world as only different shades of grey. That is until recently.
Neil now has the ability to see using his _______(5). He has implanted an antenna into his skull. It’s not attached to a headband or a hat. The antenna is _______(6) directly to the back of his skull at one end, bends over the top of his head, and has a light sensor on the other end. This light sensor _______(7) the colors and sends this information to a chip embedded in his skull. The chip _______(8) these colors into a sound. This allows Neil to experience each color as its own _______(9) sound. The red of a _______(10) light translates into one tone, while the green of a tree translates into a different tone. In this way, he has created a sound _______(11) for all the colors we see with our eyes.
Neil’s translation of color into sound has become so _______(12) that it also works in reverse. When he hears sounds, they translate into colors for him. When a telephone _______(13) or a glass breaks, he experiences these sounds as color. As an artist, this blending of sight and sound has allowed him to create unique _______(14) of art. Neil is a trained musician, and he creates sound portraits by translating the colors in paintings and photos _______(15) sounds. He also is a painter and has painted all kinds of sounds including human voices. He once painted a _______(16) by Martin Luther King and another by Hitler.
The definition of a cyborg is someone who is part human and part _______(17). Neil embraces his cyborg identity fully. He says, "I don’t feel like I’m _______(18) technology or wearing technology. I feel like I am technology. I don’t think of my antenna as a _______(19) – it’s a body part". Some people believe that humans have stopped _______(20), but perhaps people like Neil are on the cutting edge of a new type of evolution.
